cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with medical image segmentation using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning representations of sequential patches, which is a machine learning task (cs.LG). The use of a gated memory propagation unit also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the method on different medical imaging modalities suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of a multi-level framework suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
